Bandera is a x86-16 bytecode virtual machine. It accepts a subset of MASM
assembly language and DOS `int 21h` interrupts.

Bandera is named after Vanderpool, the codename for Intel's x86 virtualization
technology [1].  Bandera is the county that Vanderpool resides in.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X86_virtualization#Intel-VT-x
